	<h1>Low Blood Pressure (Hypotension)</h1>
	<p>Low blood pressure, or hypotension, occurs when your blood pressure is lower than normal.</p>
	
	<h2>Symptoms:</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Dizziness or lightheadedness</li>
		<li>Fainting or near-fainting</li>
		<li>Fatigue or weakness</li>
		<li>Rapid heartbeat</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h2>Causes:</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Dehydration</li>
		<li>Medications</li>
		<li>Heart problems</li>
		<li>Nutritional deficiencies</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h2>When to Seek Help:</h2>
	<p>If you experience severe symptoms or persistent low blood pressure, consult a healthcare professional.</p>
